<h3>Putin's war has triggered an exodus out of Russia -- but the escape options are shrinking</h3>
<h4>"How to leave Russia?" Google searches for this term in Russian hit a 10-year high inside the country within a week of the invasion of Ukraine on February 24.

    From Moscow to the Siberian oil capital of Novosibirsk, and from the intellectual hub of St. Petersburg to the nuclear submarine base of Murmansk, Russians are searching for a way out in anticipation of a grim future in a country torn apart by isolation,
     censorship and belligerence.</h4>
